						<summary>

						<p>On a rock overhanging the <hi rend="italic">Pañchapāṇḍavar-paḍukkai.</hi></p>						

						<p>There are three fragmentary inscriptions engraved on this cave. They record the beds to be carved. These inscriptions may palaeographically be assigned to c. 2nd century B.C.</p>						

						<p>The first inscription reads ••••• <hi rend="italic">paḷiy-koṭupi •••••</hi></p>						

						<p>This refers to the gift of a <hi rend="italic">paḷḷi</hi> (cave). The second inscription reads <hi rend="italic">•••• nūṟu kāchāṉa</hi> meaning the gift of one hundred <hi rend="italic">kārshāpaṇa</hi> coins.</p>						

						<p>The third inscription reads <hi rend="italic">••••• nataṉ āk-iya nāllu irukai</hi> meaning the four beds (seats) were caused to be made by ••••• nataṉ.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
